The trial of three men in connection with the Rhodes Park murder in October last year is expected to continue in the High Court in Palm Ridge on Thursday.Admore Ndlovu, 23, Thabo Nkala, 25, and Mduduzi Mathibela Lawrence, 32, were charged with robbery with aggravating circumstances, rape, and murder, all three suspects pleaded not guilty.The three men were arrested out of a gang of 12 men after they allegedly attacked two couples at Rhodes Park, East of Johannesburg on the evening of Saturday, October 17 2015 after a church service.The four victims were reportedly forced to lie on the ground and a knife was used to cut off the underwear of both women before they were raped.Their husbands, Zukisa Khela and Sizwe Tyeke, were forced to strip and ordered into the lake, where they drowned.One of the women was allegedly raped while the other woman managed to escape.CCTV footage showed several men running along Naiad Street soon after they allegedly drowned two men in a lake at Rhodes Park and sexually assaulted and raped their wives was on Wednesday shown to the High Court sitting at the Palm Ridge Magistrate s Court.TNA Reporter